<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-128-270 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 911 330</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 17 1991 n646 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Philips offers automatic tester. (application-specific integratedsupport group of Philips Communications Systems introducesScanPlus software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woolnough, Roger.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>P-ASIC, the ASIC support group of Philips Communication Systems, adivision of Philips Electronics NV, introduces ScanPlus, anautomatic test-pattern-generation package (ATPG).andP;  The P-ASICsupport group provides ASIC design services, tools and support toboth in-house and third-party systems designers.andP;  The group'smajor product is the P-ASIC Design Flow (PDF) digital-ASIC designmethodology and its integrated tool set.andP;  ScanPlus is a recentaddition to PDF.andP;  The ATPG package includes tools for extractingtest blocks from a circuit design data base, generating testpatterns for each functional block, transferring the test patternsfor each block to the terminals of the chip design and addingtester-specific timing.andP;  The original chip design is resimulatedwith results compared to those predicted by ScanPlus'stest-generation algorithm.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Philips Gloeilampenfabrieken N.V. Philips Communication Systems(Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    PHG.andO;Product:   ScanPlus (Debugging/testing software) (Product introduction)P-ASIC Design Flow (CAE software) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionTest Data GeneratorsAdd-In/On SoftwareCircuit Design.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>